Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.3dec7735-c31f-4716-8a70-1fbbf10e0fb2.prompt=User Identifier 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.4ea235b9-9ea4-4ec3-855d-4f7fd58098a2.prompt=User Identifier 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.5a26270f-2d65-4e2f-8888-d735e0de496b.description=Changes a VM's power state. Must specify either hostSystem, clusterName, or vmResourcePool as a target location for VMs. Input Parameters\: vmName - name of the VM that will be created with this flow templateName - name of the VM template to clone in vCenter osType - linux or windows host - vCenter host to execute against user - vCenter username password - vCenter password vmDatacenter - target Datacenter on the vCenter host for the VMs dataStore - target datastore on the vCenter host for the VMs hostSystem - target ESX host for the VMs clusterName - target cluster for the VMs vmResourcePool - target resource pool for the VMs vmPowerState - the desired power state (on / off etc) Responses\: success - if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0 failure - otherwise Result Fields\: serviceXml - xml representation of the server created in vCenter 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.5abcb407-10f9-4e7c-af24-430454c15895.description=This workflow adds/updates the component property using Artifact APIs. onlyUpdate\: yes/no yes - To update values of existing property (In this case input "valueType" is not required , This input will not be considered even if provided) no - To add/update property valueType - Value type of the property. It can have value from selection list "CSA-Property-ValueType". This Input is required only when Input "onlyUpdate" is selected as "no". values - One or more values dilimited by comma , (If user want to use some other separator for multiple values then needs to be pass as next input "separator") separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the values ( default dilimiter used is comma ,) 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.6e7ceffe-594f-4bbb-b3b7-afa16d3d0dbf.prompt=User Identifier 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.6e7e79dc-5c30-4d9a-9b28-8b60f0482b1f.prompt=Process Instance ID 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.7a46a508-ffc8-4400-9813-51df83395e61.prompt=User Identifier 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.7d2d9484-01f1-44ec-a8ff-b568af1bff39.prompt=User Identifier 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.81cba40e-87fe-4bde-ac91-373bfcf555e8.prompt=Process Instance ID 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.8c1d2851-8f74-45d5-84e2-b8b09f90d344.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API. Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.98a9fa8f-254b-44cb-b555-ccce8b661fcc.prompt=Resource Provider ID 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.a7dda173-3d31-4638-8f0c-ec4cd002d476.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.cbcfff5c-a627-4b46-ad15-1030d2c39ee0.prompt=Process Instance ID 29b5566d-a315-48a0-adf7-95419fd27867.description=
Start the Virtual Machine

Inputs Parameters\:

 CSA_CONTEXT_ID – CSA Context Id
 CSA_PROCESS_ID – CSA Process Instance Id
 SVC_COMPONENT_ID - This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
 RSC_PROVIDER_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL - This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
 RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time.
  		Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE - This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
 RSC_POOL_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
 SVC_INSTANCE_ID - This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 PRN_COMPONENT_ID – This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
 REQ_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
 REQ_USER_ID - This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
 USR_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
 RSC_BINDING_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.
